name: Spider Plant
description: This clump-forming, perennial, herbaceous plant, native to coastal areas of South Africa, has narrow, strap-shaped leaves arising from a central point. The leaves may be solid green or variegated with lengthwise stripes of white or yellow. The leaves are not flat, but appear channeled or folded down the middle
care_guide: Allow the top layer of soil to dry before watering. Thrives in bright, indirect sunlight.

name: Snake Plant
description: It has web-like underground roots and thick, sword-shaped leaves with a unique banded pattern. It can flower once a year, producing clusters of cream-coloured flowers, that may develop into small orange fruit
care_guide: Water sparingly and allow the soil to dry out completely between waterings. Ideal for low to bright indirect light.

name: Peace Lily
description: Peace lilies are appreciated for their glossy green leaves and white blooms, which also help improve indoor air quality.
care_guide: Keep soil consistently moist and place in low to medium light. Avoid direct sunlight to prevent leaf burn.

name: Pothos
description: Pothos features heart-shaped leaves and a trailing habit, making it perfect for shelves or hanging baskets.
care_guide: Water when the top inch of soil dries out. Tolerates low light but prefers medium, indirect light.

name: ZZ Plant
description: ZZ plants are extremely hardy, featuring glossy, dark green leaves. They are excellent for low-light environments.
care_guide: Water sparingly and allow the soil to dry out between waterings. Avoid direct sunlight.

name: Rubber Plant
description: Rubber plants have large, shiny leaves that add a dramatic flair to indoor spaces.
care_guide: Water when the topsoil is dry and place in bright, indirect light. Wipe leaves occasionally to remove dust.

name: Aloe Vera
description: Aloe vera is known for its medicinal gel and thick, fleshy leaves. It thrives with minimal care.
care_guide: Place in bright, direct sunlight and water sparingly. Ensure the pot has proper drainage.

name: Fiddle Leaf Fig
description: Fiddle leaf figs are popular for their large, violin-shaped leaves that make a bold statement indoors.
care_guide: Needs bright, filtered light and consistent watering. Avoid sudden changes in light or temperature.

name: Boston Fern
description: Boston ferns have lush, arching fronds and thrive in humid environments, making them great for bathrooms.
care_guide: Keep the soil moist and provide a humid environment. Avoid direct sunlight which can scorch the fronds.

name: English Ivy
description: English ivy features trailing vines and small, lobed leaves. It can also be used as a decorative topiary.
care_guide: Prefers cooler temperatures and moderate watering. Best kept in bright, indirect light.

name: Chinese Evergreen
description: Chinese evergreens are admired for their attractive, patterned leaves and adaptability to low-light conditions.
care_guide: Water when the top inch of soil is dry and maintain moderate light levels.

name: Philodendron
description: Philodendrons are versatile indoor plants with heart-shaped leaves and an easy-going nature.
care_guide: Water when the topsoil dries out and place in indirect light for best growth.

name: Dracaena
description: Dracaenas are known for their striking, sword-like leaves and architectural appearance, suitable for modern interiors.
care_guide: Allow the soil to dry between waterings and keep in low to bright indirect light.

name: Parlor Palm
description: Parlor palms are compact and elegant palms that add a tropical touch to indoor spaces.
care_guide: Keep soil evenly moist and provide low light conditions for optimal growth.

name: African Violet
description: African violets are beloved for their soft, fuzzy leaves and clusters of vibrant blooms.
care_guide: Water from the bottom to avoid leaf damage and keep in moderate, indirect light.

name: Bamboo Palm
description: Bamboo palms feature feather-like fronds that add a lush, tropical look to indoor environments.
care_guide: Keep soil moist and place in bright, indirect light. They also benefit from regular misting.

name: Kentia Palm
description: Kentia palms are elegant and low-maintenance, ideal for adding a refined tropical vibe to your home.
care_guide: Water regularly and avoid direct sunlight; they do well in moderate indoor light.

name: Cast Iron Plant
description: Cast iron plants are celebrated for their durability, thriving in low light and neglectful watering conditions.
care_guide: Water sparingly and tolerate low light conditions, making them ideal for dim rooms.

name: Dwarf Date Palm
description: Dwarf date palms bring a tropical ambiance with their slender trunks and feathery fronds.
care_guide: Water moderately and place in bright, indirect light for best growth.

name: Prayer Plant
description: Prayer plants are known for their uniquely patterned leaves that fold up at night, resembling praying hands.
care_guide: Keep the soil consistently moist and provide medium, indirect light.

name: Ponytail Palm
description: Ponytail palms have a distinctive swollen base with long, arching, strap-like leaves, offering a quirky look.
care_guide: Water sparingly and provide bright, indirect light; they are very drought tolerant.

name: Hoya
description: Hoyas, or wax plants, are admired for their thick, waxy leaves and clusters of star-shaped flowers.
care_guide: Allow the soil to dry out between waterings and keep in bright, indirect light.

name: Birds Nest Fern
description: Birds nest ferns feature broad, wavy fronds that form a nest-like pattern, perfect for adding softness to interiors.
care_guide: Keep the soil consistently moist and provide indirect, moderate light.

name: Moth Orchid
description: Moth orchids are popular for their elegant, long-lasting blooms and ease of care compared to other orchids.
care_guide: Water when the top of the soil feels dry and place in bright, indirect light to encourage blooming.

name: Burros Tail
description: Burros tail features trailing, fleshy stems that are perfect for hanging baskets or shelves.
care_guide: Water sparingly and provide bright, indirect sunlight. Ensure well-draining soil.

name: String of Pearls
description: String of Pearls is known for its unique, bead-like leaves that trail delicately, ideal for creative displays.
care_guide: Allow the soil to dry between waterings and provide bright light for optimal growth.

name: Christmas Cactus
description: Christmas cactus produces vibrant blooms around the holiday season and has segmented, flattened stems.
care_guide: Water when the soil is dry and maintain bright, indirect light. Avoid overwatering.

name: Succulents
description: A variety of succulent species that store water in their fleshy leaves, ideal for low-maintenance indoor gardening.
care_guide: Water sparingly and ensure plenty of sunlight. Group similar watering needs together.

name: Lucky Bamboo
description: Lucky bamboo is actually a dracaena that thrives in water or soil, often used in Feng Shui for positive energy.
care_guide: Keep the roots submerged in water or moist soil and provide low, indirect light.

name: Peperomia
description: Peperomia offers attractive, compact foliage in a variety of textures and colors, perfect for small spaces.
care_guide: Allow the top inch of soil to dry between waterings and keep in moderate, indirect light.
